crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects a Linux backdoor named Fipps used by Andariel
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: CISA.gov

attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2, for GNU/Linux 2.6.18, BuildID[sha1]=2c46d3c40075dc7a193f8041f9458b40fd1f31cf, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert icmp $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any ( msg:"PROTOCOL-ICMP Destination Unreachable Host Unreachable"; icode:1; itype:3; metadata:ruleset community; classtype:misc-activity; sid:399; rev:9; )

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a Linux backdoor/RAT that establishes a connection to a hardcoded C2 server at 185.29.10.38 on port 53. It receives commands to perform various malicious actions, including executing a remote shell by spawning `/bin/sh` (masquerading as `dbus-statd`), conducting system reconnaissance (`id`, `uname`), performing file system operations (recursive directory listing, file upload/download, deletion), and executing a port scanner against other targets.
